    feat: Phase C — MiroFish 5-step verification chain with ProposalQueue UI
    
    PART 1 — Migration (031_create_mirofish.sql):
      Extends agent_proposals with deferred status, impact_level text column,
      reviewed_at/reviewed_by, rejection_reason, step_notes. Backfills
      impact_level from impact_score. Adds queue and history indexes.
    
    PART 2 — MiroFish service extensions:
      Added deferProposal(), getProposalHistory(), PROPOSAL_APPROVED event
      emission on confirmProposal(). Updated getPendingProposals() to include
      deferred status and sort by impact DESC, created ASC.
    
    PART 3 — SCOUT gap detection:
      Added detectGap() with 8 gap pattern categories, auto-submit to MiroFish
      pipeline with automated NEXUS review. initScoutAutoDetection() subscribes
      to DATA_GAP_DETECTED and COMPLIANCE_FLAG events. Exposed window.__scout
      global for manual testing.
    
    PART 4 — ProposalQueue component:
      Mobile-first card queue with impact badges, step dots (1-5), inline
      approve/reject/defer. Inline confirmation flow (no modals). Collapsible
      history section showing last 10 approved/rejected. Empty state with
      pulse indicator.
    
    PART 5 — NEXUS proposal integration:
      Added isProposalQuery detection before branch queries. Renders pending
      proposals as branch cards with relevance coloring. Handles empty state.
    
    PART 6 — Post-approval execution hook:
      Added PROPOSAL_APPROVED + PROPOSAL_REJECTED event types to agentEventBus.
      initPostApprovalHook() logs approval, creates auto-snapshot, and emits
      targeted event to the proposing agent for execution.
    
